              "action": "Complete the Post-Event Recovery Sequence at the fitness club immediately after your next workout or practice session. Hold each pose for eight slow breaths, focusing on releasing tension rather than deepening the stretch. Record how each area (hips, shoulders, low back) feels on a 1–5 tightness scale before and after.",
              "tool": "Post-Event Recovery Sequence Guide: a step-by-step illustrated card with six gentle poses (Reclined Pigeon, Seated Twist, Supported Child's Pose, Thread the Needle, Supine Figure Four, Legs Up the Wall) including hold times, breath cues, and a before/after tightness tracker."
